article.headline: Richmond 52, William & Mary 50
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Gaston Moliva's layup with 24 seconds remaining and a free throw by Jermaine Bucknor sealed Richmond's 52-50 win over William and Mary on Saturday. Brian Hutt missed a jumper at the buzzer that would have tied the game. Richmond (6-6) won despite an 11:38 field goal drought midway through the game. Oumar Sylla's layup with 10:10 remaining ended the dry spell for Richmond, then the Tribe (5-6) went cold and could manage only two field goals in the game's final 8:50. One of those, a layup by Corey Cofield, drew William and Mary to 51-50 before Bucknor sank one of two free throws. Bucknor and Jarhon Giddings each had 11 points for Richmond Calvin Baker led the Tribe with 9 points. Richmond held William and Mary without a 3-pointer for the first time this season, while the Spiders were 7-for-18 from 3-point range.
